                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2131/284: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 8, 1935—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Department’s No. 5, January 24, 8 p.m. The Department is gratified to learn
                    from your telegram No. 19 of February 5, 10 a.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d454fn9">Not
                        printed.</note> that the Colombian Government plans to expedite conclusion
                    of Trade Agreement. Has the Government indicated any modifications or
                    suggestions with respect to the draft agreement or intimated whether it desires
                    the Department to send an expert to Bogotá?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
